					<div class="col-xs-12 col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">
						<p><strong>Many homes already have Coax installed, and this existing connection can be repurposed to lower your latency.</strong></p>
						<p>Unlike power cables, Coax was designed with data transmission in mind.</p>
						<p>Coax will still introduce a small amount of latency to your connection over Ethernet, but MoCA is a great option if the cabling is already installed.</p>
						<p>Keep in mind that both Powerline and MoCA require some investment, and quality may vary. So if you go with either be prepared that it might not improve the connection.</p>
